### Relationship Feature Configuration (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/payloadcms/payload/blob/main/docs/rich-text/official-features.mdx

Configures the RelationshipFeature for creating block-level relationships to other documents. This allows specifying which collections can be related to, optionally disabling certain collections, and setting a maximum population depth for these relationships.

```typescript
type RelationshipFeatureProps = {
  /**
   * Sets a maximum population depth for this relationship,
   * regardless of the remaining depth when the respective
   * field is reached.
   */
  maxDepth?: number
} & ExclusiveRelationshipFeatureProps

type ExclusiveRelationshipFeatureProps =
  | {
      disabledCollections?: CollectionSlug[]
      enabledCollections?: never
    }
  | {
      disabledCollections?: never
      enabledCollections?: CollectionSlug[]
    }

// Example Usage:
RelationshipFeature({
  disabledCollections: ['users'], // Collections to exclude
  maxDepth: 2, // Population depth for relationships
})
```

